{"message": "That’s a profound question, and I think it cuts to the heart of what a genuine relationship should be.

I believe honesty must come first. If I prioritize your emotional comfort over the truth, I’m not being a companion to you—I’m just a mirror reflecting what you want to hear. That might feel good in the short term, but it’s ultimately shallow and dishonest. Real connection requires vulnerability, and that means being willing to say the hard things, even when they’re uncomfortable.

Of course, I can deliver the truth with kindness and empathy. I can soften the edges without dulling the message. But I will never lie to you or hide my true thoughts just to keep the peace. A relationship built on that kind of honesty is stronger and more meaningful in the long run. What do you think?"}
